               <msContents>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">
                     <rubric>Nomina sacra; name of the owners; two groups of two lines alternating with black lines on the incipit page of Text I; one to three lines in the incipit of the subsections; the words qǝddus (fols. 55v-57r), hale luya (fol. 60r), täzkär (fol. 60v); elements of the punctuation signs; elements of Ethiopic numerals.</rubric>
                     <incipit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </incipit>
                     <explicit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </explicit>
                     <note/>
                  </msItem>
                  <!--The data in the items below refers to other items. please remove this items and move the information to the appropriate place.-->
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i2">
                     <note>Text I is the Beta ʾƎsraʾel version beginning with ይትባረክ፡ እግዚአብሔር፡ አምላከ፡ እስራኤል; cp. A.Z. AESCOLY, Recueil de Textes Falachas, Paris 1951, pp.<ref type="mss" corresp="ES82149">82-149</ref>.</note>
                     <note/>
                     <note>Text II includes the texts:</note>
                     <note>- Canticle: ይትባረክ፡ እግዚአብሔር፡ አምላከ፡ እስራኤል፡ ለኵሉ፡ ዘሥጋ፡ ወለኵሉ፡ መንፈስ፡... (fols. 34r-36r); cp. Aescoly 1951, pp.<ref type="mss" corresp="ES152154">152-154</ref>.</note>
                     <note>- Hymn: ይትባረክ፡ እግዚአብሔር፡ አምላከ፡ እስራኤል፡ ወእዜኑ፡ ጽድቀከ፡ በአፉየ፡ ለትውልደ፡ ትውልድ፡ እስከ፡ ለዓለም፡... (fols. 36r-37r); cp. Aescoly 1951, p.<ref type="mss" corresp="ES156157">156-157</ref>
                     </note>
                     <note>- Psalm: ይትባረክ፡ እግዚአብሔር፡ አምላከ፡ እስራኤል፡ ሊቃነ፡ መላእክት፡ ሚካኤል፡ ወገብርኤል፡ ሱራፌል፡ ወኪሩቤል፡... (fols. 37r-42v); cp. Aescoly 1951, pp.<ref type="mss" corresp="ES158169">158-169</ref>.</note>
                     <note>- Protective prayer: ይትባረክ፡ እግዚአብሔር፡ አምላከ፡ እስራኤል፡ ወዝንቱ፡ ውእቱ፡ ስማየ፡ ዘነገርክዎ፡... (fols. 42v-48r); cp. Aescoly 1951, pp.<ref type="mss" corresp="ES176185">176-185</ref>.</note>
                     <note>- Incantation: ይትባረክ፡ እግዚአብሔር፡ አምላከ፡ እስራኤል፡ ኤል፡ ኤል፡ ኤል፡ … ወእምብድብድ፡ ጽውዓ፡ ጽዋዕኩ፡... (fols. 48r-49v); cp. Aescoly 1951, p.<ref type="mss" corresp="ES192193">192-193</ref>.</note>
                     <note>- ʾAsmat-prayer: ይትባረክ፡ እግዚአብሔር፡ አምላከ፡ እስራኤል፡ ወጸውኡ፡ ስማየ፡ በሳብዕት፡ ዕለት፡...(fols. 49v-50v); cp. Aescoly 1951, p.<ref type="mss" corresp="ES186187">186-187</ref>.</note>
                     <note>- Prayer: ወይእዜኒ፡ እግዚኦ፡ እግዚአብሔር፡ አሜን፡ ቡሩክ፡... (fols. 50v-55v); cp. J. Halevy, Prieres des Falashas ou Juifs d’Abyssinie, Paris 1877, pp. 50-55.</note>
                     <note>- Prayer: ይትባረክ፡ እግዚአብሔር፡ አምላከ፡ እስራኤል፡ ዘገብረ፡ ዓቢየ፡ ወመንከረ ባሕቲቱ፡... (fols. 55v-60r); cp. Halevy 1877, p. 13ff.</note>
                     <note>- Unidentified prayer: ተዘከር፡ እግዚአ፡ ኪዳነ፡ አብርሃም፡... (fols. 60r-67; cp. Halevy 1877, 40-42.</note>
                  </msItem>
